name: 爱丽丝·基娜·迪尔
name_full: 爱丽丝·基娜·迪尔 Alice Kina Diehl
introduction: Alice Diehl was the winner of the Media Access Office, first annual John Ritter Scholarship for young Actors with disabilities in 2003 at the age of 16 for her work in theater arts. She also ran her very own cable access show about film in Northern California for a number of years until she eventually moved to Southern California in 2005. Where she was given another a scholarship to study under Laura Gardner at the Howard Fine Acting Studio in Hollywood. Whilst continuing to climb up the film/television ladder, Alice is also a veteran scare actor for the Reign of Terror Haunted house in Thousand Oaks, California. This haunt was ranked top 10 in all of the United States. 1/14/2018
